So is there something as "state of the art" as whisper but for text to speech/audio?

Ask HN: Why do we do orthographic mistakes on keyboard but not in handwriting?
text:
This is something that's troubled me for some time. Whether I write in English or in my native language, I sometimes make gross orthographic mistakes which are clearly pronounciation-relate, for instance I would write "sean" for "seen" or "plaid" for "played".

I have noticed that I am not the only one.

However, this never happens when manually writing with a pen.

That seems to indicate that somehow, keyboard-typing or manual-handwriting are a different brain operation/circuit.

Show HN erxes – open source Hubspot alternative
text:
Hi HN family ! We are Nauren, BJ, and MJ from erxes - open source Hubspot alternative enables SaaS providers and digital marketing agencies/developers to create unique experiences for their entire business.

We’re recently launched our product erxes XOS v.1.0, though we've in the industry for a while and started with the mission of making marketing technology accessible for all companies at any stage, including the ones in their early days.

Though due to marketing being inextricably linked to other aspects of business such as finance, core operations, and human resources, we’ve ended up expanding our business scope to include many additional features and improvements that are non-marketing upon the request of our clients. We now have EXM (employee experience management), PXM (product experience management), and delivery, which goes on and on…

This is why, today, you can not fully define erxes as marketing software anymore. It is now an experience operating system.

After +58 enterprise clients, +60 new features, +480 Active SaaS signups, and +1M installs, +$2.8M raised in the pre-seed round, we began to realize it was time to focus on the community and are transferring bootstrap enterprise-focused OS project to community-driven one.

With our Marketplace, where you can learn about all of the plugins erxes provides, as well as place your plugins and earn income from the sales.

Plugins are features that can work independently to fulfill the particular purpose of enterprises/developers, such as sales pipeline, delivery, etc. We have 30+ plugins on our marketplace right now, and more plugins will be added daily.

You can also develop your plugins to place them in the Marketplace. So, that can increase the source of your revenue.

We would love that the HN community to take a look at what we've been up to, and looking forward to hearing your feedback.

Best,

Nauren, BJ, and MJ
